OL,3,CScotland's relationship with Union at
OL,4,Cstake as vote counting begins
OL,6,FOne Reform supporter at Dewars Centre
OL,7,Fin Perth told me they're feeling
OL,8,F"positive". They will be dividing the
OL,9,Fconservative, unionist vote here,
OL,10,Fwhich usually comes second to the SNP.
OL,12,FThey told me they are "baffled" that
OL,13,Fpeople are still voting for the SNP
OL,14,Fgiven their list of "failures".
OL,16,FMeanwhile, the Scottish Conservatives
OL,17,Fare expected to see their vote share
OL,18,Fdrift away.
