OL,3,CScotland's relationship with Union at
OL,4,Cstake as vote counting begins
OL,6,FIf they fare well, Sarwar will stand
OL,7,Fby his decision to distance himself
OL,8,Ffrom the PM.
OL,10,FWill Glasgow turn green?
OL,12,FGlasgow, normally a comfortable home
OL,13,Ffor the SNP will be one to keep an eye
OL,14,Fon.
OL,16,FThe Scottish Greens are expected to
OL,17,Fmake gains in the city. If the SNP
OL,18,Fdon't get a majority of 65 seats, they
OL,19,Fwill be looking to the Scottish Greens
OL,20,Ffor pro-independence support at
OL,21,FHolyrood.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
